<script type="application/ld+json">{JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the median house price in Red Hill Brisbane?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Red Hill's median house price reflects strong demand for elevated inner-north properties with city views and character architecture. Pricing varies considerably depending on whether the property has been renovated, the aspect and view lines, and block size. Properties on the upper streets commanding direct city outlooks consistently attract premium buyer interest. An appraisal gives you an accurate read on where your home sits relative to current sales." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How long does it take to sell a home in Red Hill?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Well-presented Red Hill homes typically sell within 25 to 40 days. The suburb's combination of city proximity, elevated views and limited supply of genuine character homes means it draws a focused buyer pool. Properties positioned correctly tend to attract competitive interest early in the campaign." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the lifestyle like in Red Hill Brisbane?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Red Hill has a quiet, residential feel that is unusual for a suburb sitting less than 3 kilometres from the CBD. Tree-lined streets, predominantly owner-occupied homes and proximity to the Kelvin Grove Urban Village give it a genuine neighbourhood character. Residents walk to cafes, the QUT Kelvin Grove campus, the Queensland Conservatorium of Music and, on a clear day, enjoy uninterrupted city and ranges views from the upper streets." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What types of homes are in Red Hill?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Red Hill is predominantly Queenslander and post-war character housing on sloping blocks. Many homes have been thoughtfully renovated to add contemporary living spaces while preserving original facades and high ceilings. There is an active renovation market here: owner-occupiers consistently compete for properties with good bones and outlook, and that competition supports strong results for sellers who present their homes well." }
    }
  ]
})}</script>

