<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I know the inner-north market well. Red Hill's buyer pool is specific: professionals who want city convenience without apartment living, renovators drawn to Queenslanders with scope, and owner-occupiers who put a real premium on outlook. Understanding that buyer profile shapes every decision I make in a campaign here.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The Kelvin Grove Urban Village is within easy walking distance, providing cafes, the QUT campus, the Queensland Conservatorium of Music and a retail precinct that has matured significantly over the past decade. Homes on the upper streets of Red Hill carry sweeping views across the CBD skyline and out to the D'Aguilar ranges, and those views directly influence value. The renovation market here is genuine and active: owner-occupiers compete hard for properties with original character and structural integrity, which means well-presented unrenovated homes can generate strong competition when priced accurately. Contemporary homes with modern fitouts also perform well, particularly where views are part of the offering.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
